<subSubSection pageId="124" pageNumber="125" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="124.[151,1437,892,1928]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,928,955]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 11.0–12.0 mm long. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[654,928,929,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Figs 364−366, 368, 369</figureCitation>
): orange pronotum (retraction of fat body be- neath cuticle gives appearance of darker markings in middle area see 
<figureCitation box="[933,1031,965,992]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Fig. 364</figureCitation>
); MS with median dark brown area; elytra brown with lateral and sutural margins and apex orange yellow; LO in 
<date box="[1009,1043,1001,1027]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">V7</date>
retracted from all margins; MPP in 
<date box="[151,185,1037,1063]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">V7</date>
short narrow and apically acute.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="124" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="124.[151,1437,892,1928]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1072,1099]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Redescription of male</emphasis>
. 11.0–12.0 mm long. Colour: pronotum and MN orange (non 
<typeStatus box="[1200,1248,1073,1099]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">type</typeStatus>
male has dingy brown markings over much of surface which may be due to retraction of fat body beneath cuticle); MS with orange margins and median dark brown area; elytra brown with yellowish orange lateral apical and sutural margins and orange marked humeri; head between eyes, antennae and palpi very dark almost black; ventral aspect of thorax dark brown; all legs brown with all tibiae and tarsi almost black; abdominal ventrites 3–5 dark brown with narrow anterior and posterior margins of each ventrite pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[824,922,1253,1280]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Fig. 369</figureCitation>
), widening in median area; LO creamy white, lateral and posterior margins of 
<date box="[526,560,1289,1315]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">V7</date>
yellowish semitransparent; tergites (
<figureCitation box="[987,1086,1289,1316]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Fig. 368</figureCitation>
) dark brown except for T7, 8 which are yellow and semitransparent. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[718,818,1325,1352]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Fig. 364</figureCitation>
): lateral margins strongly divergent posteriorly (C&gt; A, B) with posterolateral corners produced a little beyond posterior margin; width subequal to humeral width. Elytron: inner two interstitial lines faintly defined; elytral punctuation not in parallel lines. Head: GHW/SIW 7/1; ASD &lt;ASW; antennal FS simple longer than wide, length&gt; GHW but not 
<date box="[910,945,1433,1459]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">2 x</date>
GHW. Mouthparts: apical labial palpomere laterally flattened of the form of a broad triangle with inner edge dentate (6 teeth). Abdomen (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Figs 365, 366, 368, 369</figureCitation>
): LO retracted from all margins of 
<date box="[619,653,1505,1531]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">V7</date>
lateral margins converge slightly posteriorly with angulate corners leading onto rounded posterior margin; MPP short narrow and apically acute. T8 parallel sided with anterolateral arms elongate slender, not bearing membranous projection on inner ventral surface; posterior margin truncate with slightly obliquely truncated corners, margin not inclining ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[917,1015,1613,1640]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Fig. 368</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1334,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Fig. 373</figureCitation>
): sternite elongate slender expanding at apex into paired sclerotized portions which end in bulbous hairy lobes. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[159,320,1685,1711]" captionStart="FIGURES 364−373" captionStartId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@125.[151,1328,166,1897]" captionTargetPageId="125" captionText="FIGURES 364−373. Pygoluciola ambita comb. nov. males. 366, 367 type male Luciola ambita (MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Figs 370−372</figureCitation>
): elongate slender widest across bases of LL; LL only slightly separated along their middorsal length and with base asymmetrical, produced strongly to left; ML reaching just beyond basal portion; apical membranous sections of LL as wide at base as at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="124.[151,1437,892,1928]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1793,1819]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier" box="[324,486,1793,1820]" firstAuthor="Olivier" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref120376" refString="Olivier, E. (1896) Descriptions de nouvelles especes de Lampyrides du Musee de Tring. Novitates Zoologicae, III (1), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1896">Olivier (1896)</bibRefCitation>
described this species with serial elytral punctures (meaning the punctures were in parallel lines). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne" box="[318,575,1829,1855]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref114336" refString="Ballantyne, L. A &amp; Jusoh, W. F. A. (2016) List of genera and species in the Luciolinae from SE Asia and the Australopacific Version 2. Checklist of IndoPacific Luciolinae, 2016, 1 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.13140 / RG. 2.1.4635.2241" type="journal article" year="2016">
Ballantyne 
<emphasis box="[447,496,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">et al</emphasis>
. (2016
</bibRefCitation>
<tableCitation box="[581,664,1829,1855]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="40.[151,239,1018,1042]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="TABLE 3. Luciolinae described as dorsally pale coloured." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/B0EB48825113187EFF0EFC65EC301854" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" tableUuid="B0EB48825113187EFF0EFC65EC301854">Table 3</tableCitation>
) addressed 12 species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1857" box="[951,1071,1829,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciolinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Luciolinae</taxonomicName>
described originally with elytral punctures in lines; of these they assigned six to a new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne. They" authorityName="Ballantyne. They" box="[817,1115,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[817,917,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Sclerotia</emphasis>
Ballantyne. They
</taxonomicName>
figured the 
<typeStatus box="[1247,1295,1865,1891]" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1896" box="[1330,1436,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambita">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">L. ambita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,261,1901,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1682,1707]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,197,1617]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,197,1619]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Key to genera characters 1. 1, 2 Australoluciola anthracina type male (MNHN); 3, 4 Aus. japenensis paratype male; 5, 6 Atyphella scabra male; 7, 8 Aty. leucura type male (MNHN). 1, 2, 5, 6 aedeagus ventral (1, 5), and dorsal (2, 6) (lateral lobes are arrowed). 3, 4, 7, 8 aedeagal sheath dorsal (3, 7), and ventral (4, 8). Oblique arrows in anterior section indicate point where tergite arms join the lateral margins of the sheath sternite; vertical arrow pointing to foot of page in 3 indicates anterior margin of sheath tergite; vertical and horizontal lines in 4 indicate length (vertical) and width (horizontal) of sheath sternite; lower paired arrows in 8 indicate emarginated margin of sheath sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508102/files/figure.png" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Figs 4−6</figureCitation>
) and dismissed, as we do here, the Olivier assertion of serial elytral punctuation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508244" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3508244" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508244/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" startId="125.[151,264,1917,1942]" targetBox="[151,1328,166,1897]" targetPageId="125">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1436,1917,2014]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,367,1917,1942]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">FIGURES 364−373.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[374,573,1917,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambita" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[374,573,1917,1941]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Pygoluciola ambita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[580,696,1918,1942]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[580,696,1918,1942]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
males. 366, 367 type male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1896" box="[977,1130,1917,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambita">Luciola ambita</taxonomicName>
(MNHN); 364, 365, 368−373 Java male (Prague). 364 habitus dorsal; 365, 366 habitus ventral; 368, 369 abdomen: 368 dorsal; 369 ventral; 370−372 ae- deagus: 370 ventral; 371 dorsal; 372 left lateral; 373 aedeagal sheath ventral with aedeagus contained. Scale lines are 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="126.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne" box="[199,463,153,180]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ballantyne" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref114336" refString="Ballantyne, L. A &amp; Jusoh, W. F. A. (2016) List of genera and species in the Luciolinae from SE Asia and the Australopacific Version 2. Checklist of IndoPacific Luciolinae, 2016, 1 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.13140 / RG. 2.1.4635.2241" type="journal article" year="2016">
Ballantyne 
<emphasis box="[327,382,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
also listed in their 
<tableCitation box="[671,753,153,179]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="42.[151,239,1404,1428]" captionTargetBox="[166,1400,1476,1861]" captionText="TABLE 4. List of species of Aquatica Fu, Ballantyne et Lambkin 2010 (*References: 1 = Fu et al. 2010; 2 = Chen 2003; 3 = Yiu 2012, 2017; 4 = Fu 2014.)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/B0EB48825111187CFF0EFAE3EB2019FF" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" tableUuid="B0EB48825111187CFF0EFAE3EB2019FF">Table 4</tableCitation>
eight genera and 21 species having a pale coloured pronotum and dark elytra with pale margins. Within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[633,719,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,719,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Luciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[727,798,189,215]" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">s. lato</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[806,998,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis box="[806,868,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">sensu</emphasis>
Ballantyne
</taxonomicName>
they listed 13 species with this colour pattern, including an Indian variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thancharoen" authorityYear="2007" box="[589,795,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquatilis">
<emphasis box="[589,795,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Sclerotia aquatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where the pale margins do not extend around the elytral apex. They were unable to reliably identify specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bugnion" authorityName="Bugnion" authorityYear="1922" box="[795,1096,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicollieri">
<emphasis box="[795,991,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Luciola nicollieri</emphasis>
Bugnion
</taxonomicName>
, which was described and figured with dark elytra having lateral and sutural margins and apex pale, pronotal width just wider than humeral width and posterolateral corners of the pronotum prolonged as in this species. However neither Bugnion’s diagrams of the ventral surface including its colouration, nor the outline of the terminal ventrites, suggest this species.
</paragraph>
